          "notes": "The module excels in narrative framing, concept accuracy, and pedagogical structure through Lessons 1-3, with compelling stories (Elite, Tron, Rogue, WFC) that ground technical concepts in real constraints and innovation. However, it catastrophically fails in D5 (Applied Outcome): Labs 1-4 are entirely empty conversational placeholders with no actual executable content, the Module Test questions 5-15 contain only placeholder buttons with no actual question text, and there is no verifiable hands-on capability demonstration. The module teaches PCG concepts well but fails to let learners practice them.",
          "topIssue": "Labs and Module Test are non-functional placeholders. Replace empty Lab sections with concrete, executable tasks (e.g., 'Use Perlin noise to generate a 256x256 height map with specified octaves and persistence; submit visualization'). Complete all 15 Module Test questions with actual question text, not placeholder buttons. Verify that learners can demonstrate a new, concrete capability (e.g., 'implement BSP dungeon generation' or 'tune noise parameters for a specific terrain type').",
